data.title: Love Island viewers slam the boy's behaviour
data.meta_description: The winter series, fronted by new host Maya Jama , kicked off in South Africa with many fans labelling the men as 'walking red flags'.
data.text:
Love Island viewers slammed the boy's behaviour just minutes after the contestants entered the villa on Monday evening.

The winter series, fronted by new host Maya Jama, kicked off in South Africa with many fans labelling the men as 'walking red flags'.

Social media users were quick to point out Shaq Muhammad's opening comment, Kai Fagan switching between three girls during the coupling, and Haris Namani and Ron Hall's 'alarming' claims that they'd 'never been in relationships.'

Security officer Shaq, 24, was the first to raise eyebrows during his VT, when he quipped: 'Can't let my girlfriend stop me from finding my wife.'

One fan of the show, echoed on Twitter: '"Cant let my girlfriend stop me from finding my wife" the flag is bright red.'

'Shaq is giving me major red flags, guys way too much,' another added.

Other's were quick to point out that many of the men in the villa had never had girlfriends before, as they discussed their relationship history on screen.

A viewer noted: 'Why tell her that youre a red flag by saying "I've never had a relationship where Ive bought any girl home.'"

'All these boys are walking red flags send them back home,' another added.

Someone else penned: 'All these men not having had relationships is the biggest red flag. Wow.'

As Kai, 24, matched with Anna-May Robey, recoupled with ring girl Olivia Hawkins, then stepped forward for for Tanyel Revan, fans also branded him a 'red flag.'

It comes after Haris has already been branded 'disrespectful' by viewers tuning in to watch Monday's launch episode.

Speaking to the group, the TV salesman, 20, boldly declared he's 'never been in a relationship'.

But eagle-eyed fans took to Twitter to call out Haris after discovering loved-up videos his ex-girlfriend Courtney Hodgson had posted on TikTok.

During his introductory video tape, he said: 'I've never had butterflies and I've never fell in love', before ruling out any single ladies whose feet were over a size five.

When asked by Maya if he's 'a relationship type of guy', he replied: 'I've never been in a relationship so it's a hard one for me'.

Taking to Twitter, one fan uploaded a video compilation of Haris with his influencer ex.

They wrote: 'nahhh not Haris saying hes never had a relationship + never brought a girl back to his #LoveIsland' (sic).

One wrote: 'Can Haris please stop openly disrespecting his ex by saying he's never had a relationship, there's videos of them on holidays all over TikTok. What a slime.'

Another said: 'Love Island finishes, open TikTok, first video - Haris and his ex Mr Ive never had a relationship this algorithm.'

A third fan chimed: 'Not Haris being exposed for lying about having a relationship already, Twitter working harder than the FBI as always'.

'Haris sitting there saying he hasnt ever been in a relationship, when his ex has exposed his dumb a*s already!', another wrote.

During the coupling up, Haris paired up with payroll administrator May Robey, 20.

Courtney, meanwhile, took to Instagram to share a photo of a huge bouquet of flowers sent to her ahead of the Love Island launch.

The influencer previously dubbed the Doncaster native the 'biggest game player' on an Instagram post announcing his participation in the reality show.
